Using Leviticus as the foundation of a right wing argument like Dr. Laura is weak.  But it is quick and when you have a radio show, I'm sure the producers would be quite miffed if she could or would really explain things.  Unless she's truly ignorant, she would know Leviticus laws have been disregarded.   They had their place in time, just like we Americans used to hang people.  Laws change, but you'd have to study a little to find out when and why.  If you didn't study, one might start bashing religion and group up with others to scream and shout that Religious people have no right to speak their thoughts and explain their beliefs.  <br>
<br>
Many of you may not be aware, but Dungeons and Dragons is considered Satins game by many &quot;pure and good&quot; Christian leaders and faithful.  So the fact that you don't get educated biblical scholars on this board is because they avoid it.  I however love to study things and have always enjoyed the stars, fantasy realms, sciences and religions.  I'd be depriving you and others much if I didn't step up and explain a few little things here about God and his endeavor to teach his people how to live life.  I'm sure Dr. Laura means well, but like each of us, she is a person and prone to make mistakes.  <br>
<br>
Does anything in the article make being gay any less a sin than it appears to be in soooo many religions?  Truth is it's still a sin in the eyes of any Christian or Jew or Muslim.  But then again, so is jealousy, desire of your neighbors wife, stealing, lying and blasphemy.  Here's a bible summary to catch anyone up to speed, so I don't speak over anyones head.<br>
<br>
OLD TEST - Frodo version:<br>
In the beginning God created man... then woman... they lived with God in peace and talked with him daily.  Then they sinned and couldn't be in his presence anymore, for he detests ALL sin.  He kicked them out, and they were on their own.<br>
<br>
Adam and Eve were taught well and lived good lives, but their children had issues.  Misguided and confused was man, so God created laws to try and help them...  these didn't help so he created judges..  they still didn't learn so he gave them Kings.. they still didn't learn so he tried more prophets.. then he was silent for 500 years before Jesus.  <br>
<br>
New Test:  Frodo's Gospel summary<br>
During the 500 years of God's silence religious leaders became very powerful and rich.  They were the ones who could read and write, they started creating many new laws and punished people in harsh ways and grew in power.  Finally God sent down his son Jesus (according to Christians).  Jesus lived a pure life, (no man of any nation has ever said otherwise).  He taught, he was crucified.  According to the Christian bible, when Jesus died, his sacrifice cleansed our sin.  God's Holy Spirit was released into man and man was given the ability to talk directly with God.  The only thing one had to do for these gifts was believe in God and his son.  Everyone who believed became free from the laws of old, for what Jesus did washed away all the past sins, and the Holy Spirit guided man instead of spiritual laws.<br>
<br>
So basically, according to the Christian faith, the letter of the law was removed.  However, once someone believes in Christ and studies the word they learn that just because the law is gone, doesn't remove sin.  Being gay isn't a greater sin than murder, nor stealing, nor lying, nor coveting your neighbors wife, nor is it less of a sin.  <br>
<br>
So, if anything this article shows us, it is that for some reason the Leviticus laws are not used anymore.  If you want to know why?  Then I suggest you go to a bible study.  If you want to bash a Jews or Christian's right to speak, then go for it.  Just remember that if they lose their right to speak, so don't we all.<br>
<br>
So for those of you who want to know if it's ok to be gay, or if I care:  No, I don't care.  The bible teachs that your life will be more difficult with sin in it.  It doesn't favor any one sin over another, it's simply more difficult with sin.  So if you're too weak to let go of some sin that is too fun to give up, that's your life.  You live it and you know what you have to put up with because of it.  If you want a better life, try giving up on a few sins and see if life gets any better. <p><img src = "http://members.socket.net/~gravy/frodoson.sig.jpg"> <BR> 52 Wanderer 
